contentrichtext.text: '''FNC''' may refer to: *FNC: The IATA airport code for [[Madeira Airport]] in Funchal, Madeira *[[FNC Inc.]], a mortgage technology company in Oxford, Mississippi *[[FNC: Uncut]], a fishing television series *[[FN FNC]], an assault rifle *[[Fabula Nova Crystallis Final Fantasy|Fabula Nova Crystallis]], an abbreviation of the project name for all upcoming Square Enix releases within the sub-series. *[[Farncombe railway station]] (station code: '''FNC''') in Godalming, England *[[Federal National Council]], the Parliament of the [[United Arab Emirates]] *[[Fédération Nationale Catholique]], a French anti-secular movement of the 1920s and 1930s *[[Fight Night Champion]], first-ever [[EA Sports]] video game to receive a mature rating *[[First Niagara Center]], an indoor arena in Buffalo, New York *[[Forum non conveniens]] *[[Fox News Channel]], an American cable and satellite news channel *[[Frazer-Nash Consultancy Ltd]] {{disambig}}
